) triangular, twice as wide at base as long in mid line ( 0.16 mm ), with bifurcate apex and concave posterior margin, disc distinctly excavate; frons 0.78 mm long, with lateral carinae close to each other; postclypeus 0.61 mm long, convex, with distinct median and lateral carinae; anteclypeus 0.48 mm long with distinct median carina; rostrum 0.92 mm long, subapical segment 4.5 times longer than apical one, apical segment as long ( 0.17 mm ) as wide; compound eyes with distinct ventral incision (
Figs. 14 & 15
